            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Wayfair (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/W\" title=\"Wayfair Inc.\">W</a></span>) set its springtime Way Day event for April 25-27. The online retailer highlighted that starting on April 20, shoppers can take advantage of lead-in daily deals that will be dropping every 24 hours, building up to three days of savings across every home category. Each day will also include flash deals. The sale will be available on Wayfair (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/W\" title=\"Wayfair Inc.\">W</a>) and across its family of brands, including AllModern, Joss &amp; Main, and Birch Lane.</p>\n<p>\"With Way Day, we're focused on delivering that confidence through quality products, strong value, and real customer feedback, so people can get their spaces ready for everything the season brings,\" noted Wayfair (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/W\" title=\"Wayfair Inc.\">W</a>) President Jon Blotner.</p>\n<p>Wayfair introduced the first Way Day on April 25, 2018. The company said it would offer major discounts across tens of thousands of home items, timed for a season when people are moving, cleaning, and refreshing their homes. In the industry, Wayfair (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/W\" title=\"Wayfair Inc.\">W</a>) was seen as inventing its own holiday to build excitement and drive sales.</p>\n<p>Shares of Wayfair (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/W\" title=\"Wayfair Inc.\">W</a>) are down more than 23% on a year-to-date basis. Short interest on the stock stands at 17.0% of the total float.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
