            "id": "4575628",
            "title": "Aligos Therapeutics jumps 22% on Greater China deal for Hepatitis B drug",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Aligos Therapeutics (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ALGS\" title=\"Aligos Therapeutics, Inc.\">ALGS</a></span>) entered into an exclusive <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20475384-aligos-therapeutics-enters-into-exclusive-license-deal-with-xiamen-amoytop-biotech-co-ltd-to\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"licensing agreement with\">licensing agreement with</a> Xiamen Amoytop Biotech Co., Ltd. to develop and commercialize pevifoscorvir sodium for chronic hepatitis B virus infection across Greater China.</li>\n<li><span>Under the terms of the agreement, Aligos (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ALGS\" title=\"Aligos Therapeutics, Inc.\">ALGS</a>) will receive an upfront milestone of $25M with the potential to earn up to $420M in additional development, regulatory, and commercial milestone payments, along with tiered high single-digit royalties on net sales in the licensed territories.</span></li>\n<li><span>Amoytop Biotech will assume responsibility for development and commercialization in Greater China, while Aligos (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ALGS\" title=\"Aligos Therapeutics, Inc.\">ALGS</a>) retains rights to the drug in other major markets, including the U.S., Europe, Japan, and South Korea.</span></li>\n<li><span>The collaboration is strategically significant given the large hepatitis B patient population in Greater China and allows Aligos to reduce development costs while extending its financial runway.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
