            "id": "4575610",
            "title": "Bank of New York Mellon sees strongest quarterly sales performance, $10B share buybacks announced",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Bank of New York Mellon (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BK\" title=\"The Bank of New York Mellon Corporation\">BK</a></span>) was trading higher as <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20475434-bny-reports-first-quarter-2026-results\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"first-quarter\">first-quarter</a> earnings surpassed analyst expectations, while sales performance saw its strongest quarter in the history of the bank.</p>\n<p>Shares were 0.77% higher at $132.97 Thursday pre-market.</p>\n<p>Adjusted diluted earnings per common share of $2.25, beating consensus by $0.32.</p>\n<p>Revenue of $5.41B (+13% Y/Y) exceeds the consensus estimate by $22M.</p>\n<p>The New York-based bank reported fee and other revenue of $4.04B, up 11% from the same quarter of 2025. The S&amp;P Cap IQ consensus estimate for noninterest income stood at $3.86B.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, net interest income of $1.37B exceeded consensus by $5M.</p>\n<p>\"BNY had a strong start to 2026 with record revenue of $5.4 billion in the first quarter, up 13% year-over-year, reflecting broad-based growth across our Securities Services and Market and Wealth Services businesses,\" said CEO Robin Vince.</p>\n<p>\"We delivered the strongest quarterly sales performance in our history, and since the beginning of the year, we announced several very strategic business wins,\" said Vince.</p>\n<p>Securities Services business segment generated a revenue of $2.68B, up 17% year-over-year. On the other hand, Market and Wealth Services business segment generated a revenue of $1.89B, 11% higher than last year.</p>\n<p>Investment and wealth management business segment saw a 6% yearly rise in revenue to $825M, while others saw a 25% jump to $16M.</p>\n<p>The CET1 ratio at the end of March 31 stood at 11.0%, down from 11.9% recorded at the end of the prior quarter.</p>\n<p>The decrease primarily reflected higher risk-weighted assets driven by a single-day increase in overnight loan balances on the last day of the quarter, along with higher client activity in agency securities lending and foreign exchange.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the board authorized a new $10B stock buyback program.</p>\n<p>Earnings conference call is scheduled to take place at 11:00 AM ET today.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4575610-bank-of-new-york-mellon-sees-strongest-quarterly-sales-performance-10b-share-buybacks-announced",
